  "text": "A usual technique to prove results of this kind is to find the centre of the largest r-star of a graph and this will prove useful to us. In this vein, Hurlbert and Kamat [CITATION_1] conjectured the following for the class of trees. Conjecture 1.2 (Hurlbert, Kamat [CITATION_2] ). Let n and r be positive integers, n ≥ r. If T is a tree on n vertices, then there is a largest r-star of T whose centre is a leaf.",
